prompts.title: Analyze and visualize data
prompts.content:
Create an interactive dashboard where I can explore our marketing performance data from the last quarter.

I've attached:
- A channel-level performance CSV
- A top-line monthly metrics CSV

The dashboard should include:

Overview
- Total revenue for the quarter
- Net new MRR
- Blended ROAS and blended CAC

Charts
- Month-over-month MRR growth with churn and net growth shown
- Channel performance comparison (spend vs revenue vs ROAS)
- Funnel velocity (leads ‚Üí opportunities ‚Üí new customers per month) if data is available

Interaction
- Filters by channel and month
- Tabs or views for:
  - Overview
  - Channel View
  - Planner / Recommendations

Design
- Clean, minimal UI (no 3D charts)
- Clear labels and tooltips

Build this as an interactive app so I can click around, change filters, and explore the data.

prompts.title: Build a prototype
prompts.content:
<prototype_requirements>
Build an interactive, clickable prototype with:
- Realistic sample data (names, numbers, dates)
- Functional navigation between all screens/sections
- Visual feedback on interactions (hover states, button clicks, form submissions)
- A polished, professional UI using a clean design system
</prototype_requirements>

<output_format>
- Single-page app (SPA) or clear multi-page structure

prompts.title: Brand Presentation
prompts.content:
Create a Google Slides presentation (10‚Äì12 slides) that tells the story of our quarter ‚Äî what worked, what didn't, and where we should double down in Q1 2026.

I've attached our Q4 2025 marketing performance data:

Include:
- Executive summary with key wins
- Channel-by-channel performance breakdown
- Month-over-month growth trajectory
- Top 3 underperforming areas with recommendations
- Q1 2026 budget reallocation proposal based on ROAS and CAC

Apply the following style guide to the presentation:

## Visual Style Guide

| Element | Specification | Usage |
|---------|---------------|-------|
| **Font** | Inter | All text elements |
| **Primary Color** | #FF6D33 | Headers, accent elements |
| **Secondary Color** | #FFCA51 | Highlights, charts |
| **Text Color** | #0F1E35 | Body text |
| **Background** | #FCF8F4 | Light backgrounds |
| **Shapes** | Rounded rectangles, 8px radius | Section dividers, buttons |
| **Images** | Create simple flat illustrations | One per major section |
| **Charts** | Minimal design, no 3D effects | Clean, executive-ready |

Make the presentation visually compelling and executive-ready. Use the data provided ‚Äî do not make up any numbers.
